Note:
Comprehensive tests for the Traceback module
:End Note

Note: Test basic exception handling
:End Note

Try:
    Let result be divide 10 by 0
    Assert false  Note: Should not reach here
:End Note
Catch Error as e:
    Let trace be format exception with exc as e
    Assert length of trace is greater than 0
    
    Call print exception with exc as e
    Call print with message as "Exception trace: " plus trace

Note: Test stack trace operations
:End Note
Let stack be extract stack trace
Assert length of stack is greater than 0

Let formatted_stack be format stack trace as stack
Assert length of formatted_stack is greater than 0

Call print stack trace as stack

Note: Test stack frame operations
:End Note
Let frames be extract stack frames
Assert length of frames is greater than 0

Let formatted_frames be format stack frames as frames
Assert length of formatted_frames is greater than 0

Call print stack frames as frames

Let current_frame be get current frame
Assert length of current_frame is greater than 0

Let caller_frame be get caller frame
Assert length of caller_frame is greater than 0

Note: Test frame information
:End Note
Let frame_info be get frame info of current_frame
Assert length of frame_info is greater than 0

Let formatted_frame be format frame as current_frame
Assert length of formatted_frame is greater than 0

Call print frame as current_frame

Note: Test exception analysis
:End Note
Try:
    Let result be access list at index 10 of empty_list
    Assert false  Note: Should not reach here
:End Note
Catch Error as e:
    Let exc_info be extract exception info from e
    Assert length of exc_info is greater than 0
    
    Let formatted_info be format exception info as exc_info
    Assert length of formatted_info is greater than 0
    
    Call print exception info as exc_info
    
    Let exc_type be get exception type of e
    Let exc_message be get exception message of e
    
    Assert length of exc_type is greater than 0
    Assert length of exc_message is greater than 0

Note: Test exception traceback
:End Note
Try:
    Let result be call non_existent_function()
    Assert false  Note: Should not reach here
:End Note
Catch Error as e:
    Let traceback be get exception traceback of e
    Assert length of traceback is greater than 0
    
    Let formatted_traceback be format exception traceback of e
    Assert length of formatted_traceback is greater than 0
    
    Call print exception traceback of e

Note: Test cause chain analysis
:End Note
Try:
    Try:
        Let result be divide 10 by 0
        Assert false  Note: Should not reach here
    :End Note
    Catch Error as inner_e:
        Let wrapped_error be "Wrapped error: " plus inner_e
        Throw wrapped_error
    :End Note
:End Note
Catch Error as e:
    Let cause_chain be extract cause chain from e
    Assert length of cause_chain is greater than 0
    
    Let formatted_chain be format cause chain as cause_chain
    Assert length of formatted_chain is greater than 0
    
    Call print cause chain as cause_chain
    
    Let root_cause be get root cause of e
    Assert length of root_cause is greater than 0
    
    Let formatted_root be format root cause as root_cause
    Assert length of formatted_root is greater than 0
    
    Call print root cause as root_cause

Note: Test stack analysis
:End Note
Let stack_for_analysis be extract stack trace
Let analysis be analyze stack trace as stack_for_analysis
Assert length of analysis is greater than 0

Let frames_for_analysis be extract stack frames
Let frame_analysis be analyze stack frames as frames_for_analysis
Assert length of frame_analysis is greater than 0

Note: Test stack depth and metrics
:End Note
Let stack_for_depth be extract stack trace
Let frames_for_depth be extract stack frames

Let stack_depth be get stack depth of stack_for_depth
Let frame_depth be get frame depth of frames_for_depth

Assert stack_depth is greater than 0
Assert frame_depth is greater than 0

Note: Test frame searching
:End Note
Let frames_for_search be extract stack frames

Let function_frame be find frame by function frames_for_search and "main"
Note: May be None if no main function in stack
:End Note

Let file_frame be find frame by file frames_for_search and "test_traceback.runa"
Note: May be None if file not in stack
:End Note

Let line_frame be find frame by line frames_for_search and 1
Note: May be None if line not in stack
:End Note

Note: Test frame filtering
:End Note
Let frames_for_filter be extract stack frames

Let function_frames be filter frames by function frames_for_filter and "test"
Let file_frames be filter frames by file frames_for_filter and "*.runa"
Let line_range_frames be filter frames by line range frames_for_filter and start_line as 1 and end_line as 100

Assert length of function_frames is greater than or equal to 0
Assert length of file_frames is greater than or equal to 0
Assert length of line_range_frames is greater than or equal to 0

Note: Test frame context
:End Note
Let current_frame_for_context be get current frame
Let context be get frame context of current_frame_for_context with context_lines as 3
Assert length of context is greater than 0

Let formatted_context be format frame context as context
Assert length of formatted_context is greater than 0

Call print frame context as context

Note: Test frame variables
:End Note
Let current_frame_for_vars be get current frame

Let variables be get frame variables of current_frame_for_vars
Assert length of variables is greater than or equal to 0

Let formatted_variables be format frame variables as variables
Assert length of formatted_variables is greater than 0

Call print frame variables as variables

Let globals be get frame globals of current_frame_for_vars
Assert length of globals is greater than or equal to 0

Let formatted_globals be format frame globals as globals
Assert length of formatted_globals is greater than 0

Call print frame globals as globals

Let arguments be get frame arguments of current_frame_for_vars
Assert length of arguments is greater than or equal to 0

Let formatted_arguments be format frame arguments as arguments
Assert length of formatted_arguments is greater than 0

Call print frame arguments as arguments

Note: Test call chain analysis
:End Note
Let frames_for_call_chain be extract stack frames
Let call_chain be extract call chain from frames_for_call_chain
Assert length of call_chain is greater than 0

Let formatted_chain be format call chain as call_chain
Assert length of formatted_chain is greater than 0

Call print call chain as call_chain

Note: Test call tree analysis
:End Note
Let frames_for_call_tree be extract stack frames
Let call_tree be get call tree from frames_for_call_tree
Assert length of call_tree is greater than 0

Let formatted_tree be format call tree as call_tree
Assert length of formatted_tree is greater than 0

Call print call tree as call_tree

Note: Test performance analysis
:End Note
Let frames_for_performance be extract stack frames
Let performance be analyze performance of frames_for_performance
Assert length of performance is greater than 0

Let formatted_performance be format performance analysis as performance
Assert length of formatted_performance is greater than 0

Call print performance analysis as performance

Note: Test cycle detection
:End Note
Let frames_for_cycles be extract stack frames
Let cycles be detect cycles in frames_for_cycles
Assert length of cycles is greater than or equal to 0

Let formatted_cycles be format cycles as cycles
Assert length of formatted_cycles is greater than 0

Call print cycles as cycles

Note: Test bottleneck detection
:End Note
Let frames_for_bottlenecks be extract stack frames
