Note: Test error reporting
:End Note
Try:
    Let result be call problematic_function()
    Assert false  Note: Should not reach here
:End Note
Catch Error as e:
    Let stack_for_report be extract stack trace
    Let error_report be create error report with exc as e and stack as stack_for_report
    Assert length of error_report is greater than 0
    
    Let formatted_report be format error report as error_report
    Assert length of formatted_report is greater than 0
    
    Call print error report as error_report

Note: Test error classification
:End Note
Try:
    Let result be call function_that_fails()
    Assert false  Note: Should not reach here
:End Note
Catch Error as e:
    Let error_class be classify error e
    Let severity be get error severity of e
    Let category be get error category of e
    
    Assert length of error_class is greater than 0
    Assert length of severity is greater than 0
    Assert length of category is greater than 0

Note: Test error suggestions
:End Note
Try:
    Let result be call function_with_issues()
    Assert false  Note: Should not reach here
:End Note
Catch Error as e:
    Let suggestions be get error suggestions for e
    Assert length of suggestions is greater than or equal to 0
    
    Let formatted_suggestions be format error suggestions as suggestions
    Assert length of formatted_suggestions is greater than 0
    
    Call print error suggestions as suggestions

Note: Test debug information
:End Note
Let debug_info be get debug info
Assert length of debug_info is greater than 0

Let formatted_debug be format debug info as debug_info
Assert length of formatted_debug is greater than 0

Call print debug info as debug_info

Note: Test debug mode management
:End Note
Enable debug mode
Assert is debug enabled is equal to true

Set debug level to "verbose"
Assert get debug level is equal to "verbose"

Add debug point with name as "checkpoint1" and data as "Important data"
Add debug point with name as "checkpoint2" and data as dictionary with "key" as "value"

Let debug_points be get debug points
Assert length of debug_points is greater than 0

Let formatted_points be format debug points as debug_points
Assert length of formatted_points is greater than 0

Call print debug points as debug_points

Clear debug points
Assert length of get debug points is equal to 0

Disable debug mode
Assert is debug enabled is equal to false

Note: Test logging support
:End Note
Let log_entry be create log entry with level as "info" and message as "Application started" and data as dictionary with "version" as "1.0"
Assert length of log_entry is greater than 0

Add log entry log_entry

Let error_entry be create log entry with level as "error" and message as "Operation failed" and data as "Error details"
Add log entry error_entry

Let log_entries be get log entries
Assert length of log_entries is greater than 0

Let formatted_entries be format log entries as log_entries
Assert length of formatted_entries is greater than 0

Call print log entries as formatted_entries

Note: Test log filtering and search
:End Note
Let all_entries be get log entries
Let error_entries be filter log entries all_entries and level as "error"
Let search_results be search log entries all_entries and pattern as "failed"

Assert length of error_entries is greater than 0
Assert length of search_results is greater than 0

Note: Test log statistics
:End Note
Let log_entries_for_stats be get log entries
Let statistics be get log statistics of log_entries_for_stats
Assert length of statistics is greater than 0

Let formatted_statistics be format log statistics as statistics
Assert length of formatted_statistics is greater than 0

Call print log statistics as statistics

Note: Test complex traceback workflow
:End Note
Process called "test_function" that takes param as String returns String:
    Let result be "Processed: " plus param
    Return result

Process called "nested_function" that takes data as String returns String:
    Let processed be test_function with param as data
    Return processed

Process called "outer_function" that takes input as String returns String:
    Let result be nested_function with data as input
    Return result

Try:
    Let result be outer_function with input as "test data"
    Call print with message as "Result: " plus result
:End Note
Catch Error as e:
    Let stack be extract stack trace
    Let frames be extract stack frames
    
    Let analysis be analyze stack frames as frames
    Let call_chain be extract call chain from frames
    
    Call print with message as "Stack depth: " plus length of stack
    Call print with message as "Frame count: " plus length of frames
    Call print with message as "Call chain: " plus call_chain
    
    Let error_report be create error report with exc as e and stack as stack
    Call print with message as "Error report created: " plus length of error_report

Note: Test error handling with debug mode
:End Note
Enable debug mode
Add debug point with name as "test_start" and data as "Starting test"

Try:
    Let result be call function_that_does_not_exist()
    Assert false  Note: Should not reach here
:End Note
Catch Error as e:
    Let debug_points be get debug points
    Assert length of debug_points is greater than 0
    
    Let error_report be create error report with exc as e and stack as extract stack trace
    Call print with message as "Debug error report: " plus length of error_report
    
    Add log entry create log entry with level as "error" and message as "Test error occurred" and data as e

Clear debug points
Disable debug mode

Note: Test performance with large stack
:End Note
Process called "recursive_function" that takes depth as Integer returns String:
    If depth is equal to 0:
        Return "Base case"
    Otherwise:
        Let result be recursive_function with depth as depth minus 1
        Return "Level " plus depth plus ": " plus result

Try:
    Let result be recursive_function with depth as 5
    Call print with message as "Recursive result: " plus result
:End Note
Catch Error as e:
    Let stack be extract stack trace
    Let frames be extract stack frames
    
    Let performance be analyze performance of frames
    Let bottlenecks be find bottlenecks in frames
    
    Call print with message as "Stack size: " plus length of stack)
    Call print with message as "Performance analysis: " plus length of performance)
    Call print with message as "Bottlenecks found: " plus length of bottlenecks)

Call print with message as "All Traceback module tests passed!" 